{\displaystyle \operatorname {sf} (n)=\prod _{k=1}^{n}k!=\prod _{k=1}^{n}k^{n-k+1}=1^{n}\cdot 2^{n-1}\cdot 3^{n-2}\cdots (n-1)^{2}\cdot n^{1}.}



Equivalently, the superfactorial is given by the formula





