{\displaystyle {\binom {n}{k}}={\frac {n^{\underline {k}}}{k!}}={\frac {n!}{(n-k)!k!}}={\frac {n^{\underline {n-k}}}{(n-k)!}}={\binom {n}{n-k}}.}






The factorial function can be shown, using the power rule, to be












n
