HedgeZ Fund Profile
































Factorial
Feeder Fund

















Fund Investment Objectives











                                        The Factorial Fund focuses on bottom-up analysis on sectors, companies and situations. Once it finds a compelling idea on which it has an edge, it looks across the capital structure, and plays this idea through the best risk-reward instruments. It puts in place hedges to make the portfolio largely market neutral. It also hedges out most of the macro risks, such as interest rates and currencies. The Fund also leverages the strong relationships built by the investing team over a decade of interaction with sell-side sales and bankers in both large international houses as well as small local houses which are normally overlooked but can be a source of information and local currency denominated transactions. Actual inception date is January 18, 2012. AUM is not disclosed. 
                                    

















 















